# HUA BOOKINGS workflow

## How we work

- The user describes what they want in plain language (no git or terminal jargon required).
- The agent implements changes in this repo, tests locally when relevant, and creates git commits when work is done.
- The agent runs `git push` when credentials allow; if push fails with auth errors, give the user the exact one-line `git push` command to run in Cursor Terminal.

## Publishing (GitHub Pages)

- Live site: `https://shahabibii.github.io/HUA-BOOKINGS/`
- Deploys from the **main** branch (root folder). Pushing **main** updates the public site in 1–2 minutes.
- After pushing, remind the user to hard-refresh the browser (Cmd+Shift+R) if they still see old UI.

## One-time GitHub setup (user)

Choose one so push works from Terminal:

1. **GitHub CLI (recommended):** Install from https://cli.github.com then run `gh auth login` and follow the browser sign-in.
2. **Personal access token:** https://github.com/settings/tokens/new — check **repo**, use the token as the password when `git push` asks for a password (username: `shahabibii`).

## Project notes

- Static site: `index.html`, `styles.css`, `app.js` — no build step.
- Local preview: `python3 -m http.server 8766` in this folder, then open http://localhost:8766/
- CSV/PDF uploads stay in the browser only (localStorage), not on GitHub.
